				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				<BR>
 <BR>
 First of all id like to correct one of the posts above mine - it says to DD then send in pet... NEVER burn before getting the pet in the heat, make sure it has the attention of your target before DDing, or you will find yourself agroed and LOADING very soon. <BR>
<BR>
Apart from that, I really wish all you guys going on about how us mages gets shafted would get real - the ONLY way you say so is either: <BR>
<BR>
1. You are lvl 5 and havent got the slightest idea what the word Conjuration means.<BR>
<BR>
2. youre not even a mage, but since you dont know how to play your current class, you go ***** over things you dont understand at the mage posts...<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
 Heres the real deal about Mages:<BR>
<BR>
yes, we ARE the number 1 class to play when it comes to pets. Put that fact together with the one that we get 2nd best nukes, and you have a very deadly combination. APART from getting that upper hand, we are almost totally self-supportive (if you see a mage shouting about where to find the food vendor - find him and kick him!)<BR>
 At lower lvls you may think that it doesnt matter to summon some bread and water, and maybe you are right - but concidering the amount of items we can summon, and their effects, we should be so happy! At later lvls ppl will beg you to summon for them, and they will remember you for doing so.<BR>
<BR>
 In groups we provide an all-round service as we summon. Solo - well, we are really never solo because we have a pet that has better stats than a warrior at the same lvl, and when that pet goes in, you will find it HARD to agro the mob on you at later lvls - that pet simply owns...<BR>
<BR>
 I guess ill stop here, as i cant tell you young mages the things we get to do at lvl 60 (the things we can do from 50 and up can not be compared to the things you are able to below 50, not even remotely!) Play that Mage - Solo, Get to know Dungeons before 35, make a positive reputation out there - and i promise you, when you reach 55, you will praise the hour in which you chose to be a Magician!<BR>
<BR>
  Cathay Elvenborn<BR>
  44 Mage<BR>
  Nomads of Asgaard<BR>
  Bristlebane<BR>
<BR>
  (a real man duels to the death!)  :p<BR>

